    "name": "Taxi Brooklyn",
    "description": "Chyler Leigh stars as hard-as-nails Det. Caitlyn \"Cat\" Sullivan, a woman hell-bent on finding her father's killer. After she's demoted to foot patrol for reckless driving, disobeying orders and personality conflicts, Cat meets taxi driver Leo Romba (Jacky Ido). A highly skilled driver, Leo is a charming French African from Marseille. Realizing Leo lied on his immigration forms, Cat offers him a deal: In exchange for his driving skills and taxi, she will help Leo with his immigration problem. In order to stay out of prison and avoid deportation, Leo agrees to partner with Cat and quickly becomes her personal driver, consultant and friend as they race through the streets of New York solving cases and trying to uncover the mystery behind her father's murder.\r\n\r\nFrom executive producers Thomas Anargyros, Edouard de Vésinne and Gary Scott-Thompson, \"Taxi Brooklyn\" is based upon the film \"Taxi\" written by Luc Besson and is a production of EuropaCorp Television with the participation of TF1.",
